% @MCCODE_PREFIX@PLOTDIFF(1)
% @FLAVOR_UPPER@ @MCCODE_PARTICLE@ Ray Tracing Team
% @MCCODE_DATE@

# NAME

**@MCCODE_PREFIX@plotdiff-pyqtgraph** - Interactively plotting the difference between two @MCCODE_NAME@ simulation results

# SYNOPSIS

**@MCCODE_PREFIX@plotdiff-pyqtgraph** [-h] [-A LABEL_A] [-B LABEL_B] [-t] [--invcanvas] a b

# DESCRIPTION

The front-end **@MCCODE_PREFIX@plotdiff-pyqtgraph** interactively browses the
*difference* between the monitors of two @MCCODE_NAME@ simulation results, i.e.
`diff.monN = a.monN - b.monN` for every monitor output file `monN` that is
present, with matching binning, in both simulation results `a` and `b`. This
is useful to quickly spot how two simulation runs differ, e.g. after a
component or parameter change, a McCode version upgrade, or comparing MPI vs.
non-MPI results.

`a` and `b` may each be either a simulation output directory (as produced by
`@MCCODE_PREFIX@run`, containing a `mccode.sim` file) or a single monitor data
file. Only monitors present in both `a` and `b`, with identical binning, are
compared; monitors found in only one of the two inputs, or with mismatched
binning, are skipped with a warning printed to the console.

This tool reuses the same interactive pyqtgraph frontend as
**@MCCODE_PREFIX@plot-pyqtgraph** (mouse/keyboard interaction, colour map
cycling, PNG/SVG export, etc. -- see the keyboard shortcuts printed on
startup, or press F1/h in the plot window), applied to the computed diff
monitors instead of a single simulation's monitors. Since difference data is
signed, 2D monitors default to a diverging blue/white/red colour map (blue =
negative, i.e. `b` bigger than `a`; red = positive, i.e. `a` bigger than
`b`); press 'c' to cycle to another colour map as usual.

# OPTIONS

**-h, --help**
:   show this help message and exit

**-A LABEL_A, --label-a LABEL_A**
:   short label used for simulation `a` in the window title (default: the
    basename of `a`)

**-B LABEL_B, --label-b LABEL_B**
:   short label used for simulation `b` in the window title (default: the
    basename of `b`)

**-t, --test**
:   mccode data loader test run (prints the diff plot graph structure)

**--invcanvas**
:   invert canvas background from black to white

# FILES

/usr/share/@FLAVOR@/resources
/usr/share/@FLAVOR@/tools/Python/mccodelib/mccode_config.json
~/.@FLAVOR@/mccode_config.json
http://www.@FLAVOR@.org

# EXAMPLES

Run the *Test_SX* example (Single crystal diffraction) twice with different parameters, and browse the difference
:   - `@MCCODE_PREFIX@run Test_SX.instr -d output_a -n 1e7 TTH=13.4`
:   - `@MCCODE_PREFIX@run Test_SX.instr -d output_b -n 1e7 TTH=14.0`
:   - `@MCCODE_PREFIX@plotdiff-pyqtgraph output_a output_b`

